        <div n="086-641L">
          <head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-086-641L-headnote-1">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-086-641L-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-086-641L-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">&#13;</l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-086-641L-headnote-2">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-086-641L-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-086-641L-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-086-641L-headnote-3">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-086-641L-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-086-641L-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-1" n="1">When Mother Clud had rise from Play</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-2" n="2">And call'd to take y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Cards away</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-3" n="3">Van Saw but seem'd not to regard</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-4" n="4">How Misse picked up each painted Card</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-5" n="5">And busy both with hand &amp; Eye</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-6" n="6">Soon rais'd a house two Storys high</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-7" n="7">Van's Genius without thought or Lecture</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-8" n="8">This hugely turn'd to Architecture</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-9" n="9">He Saw y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Edifice &amp; Smild</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-10" n="10">Vow'd it was prety for a Child;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-11" n="11">It was so perfect in \<hi rend="italics">del</hi>·its·<hi rend="italics">add</hi>·y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi>\ kind</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-12" n="12">He kept y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Modell in his mind.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-13" n="13">But when he found y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Boys at Play</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-14" n="14">And saw them dabling in y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Clay</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-15" n="15">He Stood behind a Stall to Lurcke</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-16" n="16">&amp; marke y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> progresse of y<hi rend="superscript">er</hi> Worke</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-17" n="17">With true delight observ'd y<hi rend="superscript">m</hi> all</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-18" n="18">Rakeing up Mudd to make a Wall</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-19" n="19">The Plan he much admir'd &amp; took</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-20" n="20">The Modell in his Table Booke.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-21" n="21">Thought himselfe now exactly Skill'd</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-22" n="22">And So resolv'd a House to build;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-23" n="23">A real house with rooms &amp; Staires</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-24" n="24">Five times at Least as big as Theirs</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-25" n="25">Taller then Miss's by two Yards,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-26" n="26">Not a Sham Thing of Clay &amp; Cards:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-27" n="27">And So he did, for in a While</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-28" n="28">He built up Such a Monstrous Pile,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-29" n="29">That no two Chairmen could be found</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-30" n="30">Able to Lift it from y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Ground.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-31" n="31">Still at Whitehall it Stands in Veiw</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-32" n="32">Just in y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Place where first it grew.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-33" n="33">There all the Little School-boys run</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-34" n="34">Envying to see themselves out done.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-35" n="35">From Such deep rudim<hi rend="superscript">ts</hi> as these</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-36" n="36">Van is become by due degrees</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-37" n="37">For Building fam'd &amp; justly reckon'd</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-38" n="38">At Court Vitruvius y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Second.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-39" n="39">No wonder Since Wise authors shew</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-40" n="40">The best foundacons must be Low.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-41" n="41">On this the Duke has wisely tan'e him</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-42" n="42">To be His Architect at Blenheim.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-43" n="43">But Raillery for once apart</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-44" n="44">If this rule holds in 'ry part</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-45" n="45">Or if His Grace were no more skill'd in</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-46" n="46">The Art of battring Wall then building,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-47" n="47">Wee might Expect to find next Year</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-641L-line-48" n="48">A Mousetrap man cheife Engeneer</l>
          </lg>
